esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert on Kubernetes Pod ExceededGracePeriod events.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Pod didn't stop gracefully within terminationGracePeriodSeconds.
//
// What it means:
// Pod was forcefully killed — may cause data loss or connection drops.
//
// Common causes:
// Hung processes, blocked shutdown hooks, unresponsive application, I/O wait.
//
// Action needed:
// Review application shutdown logic, check for blocking operations, adjust grace period.
//
// To scope to a namespace, add: AND `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace` == "YOUR_NAMESPACE"
FROM metrics-kubernetes.event-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind` == "Pod"
  AND `kubernetes.event.source.component` == "kubelet"
  AND `kubernetes.event.reason` == "ExceededGracePeriod"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace`,
     `kubernetes.event.involved_object.name`, `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind`,
     `kubernetes.event.reason`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
